Daily energy expenditure was estimated using the factorial approach [20]. Here, each of the 12 codes, which had a corresponding metabolic equivalent (MET) value, was assigned a Physical Activity Level (PAL) [21] and a daily PAL was determined by multiplying each of the 12 codes by the total amount of time spent at the activity level. Where he had made notes on a specific sport and exercise activity undertaken during the 4 days, the Compendium of Physical Activities [22] was used to calculate the specific PAL value. Daily energy expenditure was then estimated by multiplying the daily PAL value by the age and sex specific resting metabolic rate (RMR; kcal/d) using height, weight and the World Health Organization (WHO) equation [23]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
